HEADWORD: Glottal
<hw>Glot"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to,
or produced by, the glottis; glottic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Glottal catch</b></col>, <cd>an effect produced upon the
breath or voice by a sudden opening or closing of the glotts.</cd>
<au>Sweet.</au></cs></p>

<p><ent>Glottidean</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Glottic</ent>⟦br⟧
